    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-03T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-03T17:00:00-05:00" n="303"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d303">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/211c</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-03T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 3, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1827. For <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">Stevens</persName> [from <persName
                        corresp="#p_WD1">Willard</persName>]:</p>
                <p>Following cable from American Consul, Tiflis, Caucasus: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Railroad conditions are deplorable and threaten famine consequence of
                            which the Consul recommends urgently that our railway commission send an
                            expert to study problem. The authorities in the Caucasus are reported to
                            be most anxious for assistance. The chief of the British Military
                            Mission, General Shore, seems to be doubtful of possibility of holding
                            the army on that front unless conditions of railroad transportation
                            improve.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>What do you think can be done? You know the kind of forces we are sending with
                        <persName corresp="#p_ECH1">Emerson</persName>. What if anything else do you
                    think we ought to do to meet the condition in the south of Russia?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
